🐳 What is Docker?

Docker is a tool used to create, run, and manage applications inside containers.

Docker helps developers package an application with:

Code

Libraries

Dependencies

Configuration files

So the app runs the same everywhere (your laptop, server, cloud).

Docker is developed by Docker, Inc..

📦 What is a Container?

A container is a lightweight, portable box that contains:

Application

All required software to run it

It works on any system where Docker is installed.

👉 Example:
If you create a Node.js app on Ubuntu, it will also run on Windows or cloud without problems using Docker.

🚀 Why Use Docker?

✅ Runs anywhere

✅ Easy deployment

✅ Saves time

✅ Lightweight (faster than Virtual Machines)

✅ Good for DevOps & Microservices

🆚 Docker vs Virtual Machine
Docker (Container)	Virtual Machine
Lightweight	Heavy
Fast startup	Slow startup
Shares OS kernel	Full OS inside
🛠 Simple Example

Without Docker:

“It works on my machine!” 😅

With Docker:

“It works everywhere!” 😎

